02/09/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The BiH Security Ministry announced on Friday (August 31st) that an agreement between BiH and NATO on the exchange of classified information became effective on August 28th. Under the deal, which was signed on March 16th between NATO Secretary-General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer and BiH Security Minister Tarik Sadovic, BiH authorities will have access to NATO information marked confidential, internal confidential and secret. No other country in the region has been given such access. (SRNA, RTRS - 31/08/07)
